				<td colspan="2"><span>Aye that works.  Remember that fear is ae so its actually a lot less risky than you might think.  Also you will get resists on fear quite a bit.  Personally when fear kiting I would prefer to fear first and snare later.  Always keep the mob feared.  Snare it when  you can, if snare is resisted go back to fear and let the mob run.  Don't try to twist anything else but fear and snare.  Use your initimidation skill when you get it.  It doesnt work often, but hey, its free!  </span></td>
